HEADWORD: Ungulata
<hw>Un`gu*la"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
L. <ets>ungula</ets> hoof.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An extensive
group of mammals including all those that have hoofs. It comprises the
Artiodactyla and Perissodactyla.</def>⟦br⟧
